\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 \strokec2 1. Purpose\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 Aleto Ads Manager is an internal tool that helps the owner of Aleto Pintores (a small painting business) create, manage and report on the company's 
\f0\b own Google Ads Search campaigns
\f1\b0 . The tool is AI-assisted: a large-language-model agent (Anthropic Claude, operated through the Claude Code environment) drafts campaign structures, ad copy and optimization proposals. 
\f0\b Every change that would modify the account (mutate operation) is reviewed and explicitly approved by the business owner before the tool executes it.
\f1\b0  The AI proposes; a human decides.\
The tool exists because the business is owner-operated with no marketing staff: AI assistance makes professional campaign management feasible, while API access makes changes auditable, scripted and reversible instead of manual dashboard edits.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 2. Users and account scope\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \'95 
\f0\b Single user:
\f1\b0  the business owner (and only the owner).\
\'95 
\f0\b Single advertiser:
\f1\b0  the tool authenticates exclusively against the Google Ads account(s) owned by Aleto Pintores, under the company's own manager (MCC) account.\
\'95 The developer token will never be used to access accounts of any other company or client. The tool is not a service offered to others; there is no signup, no multi-tenant capability, and no plan to resell or white-label it.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 3. Functional description\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\fs28 \cf0 3.1 What the tool does\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 1. 
\f0\b Campaign creation
\f1\b0  \'97 builds Search campaigns for the company's painting services (interior painting, gotel\'e9 removal, door lacquering, facade painting) targeting Madrid, Spain: campaigns, ad groups, keywords, negative keywords, responsive search ads, sitelinks and budgets.\
2. 
\f0\b Campaign management
\f1\b0  \'97 pauses/enables entities, adjusts budgets and bids (Smart Bidding configurations), updates ad copy, adds negative keywords derived from search-term reports.\
3. 
\f0\b Reporting
\f1\b0  \'97 retrieves performance reports (impressions, clicks, cost, conversions, search terms) for internal analysis and for the owner's weekly review.\
4. 
\f0\b Conversion management
\f1\b0  \'97 creates and maintains the company's own conversion actions (WhatsApp click, phone click, quote-form submission), which are fired from the company website.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa280\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs28 \cf0 3.2 What the tool deliberately does NOT do\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 \'95 No access to third-party accounts; no cross-account data mixing.\
\'95 No automated spend increases: budget changes always require explicit owner approval.\
\'95 No scraped or purchased audience data; no upload of third-party user data.\
\'95 No fully autonomous mutations: the AI agent cannot execute a mutate call without a human approval step (see \'a75).\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 4. Architecture\
\pard\pardeftab720\partightenfactor0

\f2\b0\fs24 \cf0 +----------------+     conversation      +---------------------+\
| Business owner | <------------------>  |  AI agent (Claude)  |\
| (approves all  |    proposals /        |  drafts campaigns,  |\
|  mutations)    |    approvals          |  analyses reports   |\
+----------------+                       +---------------------+\
                                                    |\
                                                    v\
                                         +---------------------+\
                                         |  API client layer   |\
                                         |  (Python,           |\
                                         |  google-ads-python  |\
                                         |  official library)  |\
                                         +---------------------+\
                                                    |\
                                     OAuth 2.0 (company credentials)\
                                     Developer token (this application)\
                                                    |\
                                                    v\
                                         +---------------------+\
                                         |   Google Ads API    |\
                                         |   (own MCC account) |\
                                         +---------------------+\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1 \cf0 \'95 
\f0\b Runtime:
\f1\b0  local workstation scripts (Python, official `google-ads` client library). No public-facing servers; no hosted SaaS component.\
\'95 
\f0\b Authentication:
\f1\b0  standard OAuth 2.0 installed-application flow with credentials from the company's own Google Cloud project; refresh token for the company's own Ads login. The developer token is used only in combination with these company-owned credentials.\
\'95 
\f0\b Reporting path is read-only;
\f1\b0  the mutation path is separated and wrapped by the approval step described in \'a75.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

\f0\b\fs36 \cf0 5. Human-in-the-loop control for AI-generated changes\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa240\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 All mutate operations follow a fixed workflow:\
1. The AI agent prepares a 
\f0\b change proposal
\f1\b0  (e.g., "create ad group 'Quitar gotel\'e9 \'97 Chamber\'ed' with these 12 keywords, this RSA copy, budget X \'80/day") rendered as a human-readable diff.\
2. The owner reviews and 
\f0\b explicitly approves or rejects
\f1\b0  the proposal in the console.\
3. Only after approval does the client layer execute the corresponding API calls, using `validateOnly` pre-checks where applicable.\
4. Every executed change is 
\f0\b logged locally
\f1\b0  (timestamp, entities affected, request summary) so the account history is fully auditable and reversible.\
\pard\pardeftab720\sa298\partightenfactor0

